headline: NTAP Q3 Deep Dive: AI and Cloud Portfolio Drive Growth Amid Macro Uncertainty
summary: Data storage company NetApp (NASDAQ:NTAP) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 2.8% year on year to $1.71 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $1.69 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.1% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.05 per share was 8.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
